VASCO Data Security International, Inc. Key Developments

VASCO Data Security International, Inc. Announces Management Changes
Jul 27 17
VASCO Data Security International, Inc. announced an that, President and Chief Operating Officer Scott Clements has been appointed President and Chief Executive Officer, effective July 28, 2017. He has also been elected to the board of directors. Mr. Clements succeeds Founder, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer T. Kendall Hunt. Mr. Hunt will continue to serve as Chairman of the Board. Mr. Clements was appointed VASCO Chief Strategy Officer in 2015. He was promoted to VASCO President and COO in November 2016. Clements joined the Company in 2015 from Tyco, where he was previously the president of the billion-dollar Retail Solutions business and the company's Chief Technology Officer.


VASCO Data Security International Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Financial Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 27 17
VASCO Data Security International Inc. reported unaudited consolidated financial results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total revenue of $45,694,000 against $54,293,000 a year ago. Operating loss was $400,000 against income of $3,386,000 a year ago. Income before income taxes was $313,000 against $3,804,000 a year ago. Net income was $110,000 against $2,825,000 a year ago. Basic and diluted income per share was $0.00 against $0.07 a year ago. EBITDA was $2,598,000 against $6,295,000 a year ago. Adjusted net income was $2,536,000 or $0.06 per diluted share against or $6,063,000 or $0.15 per Diluted share a year ago.

For the six months, the company reported revenue of $66,032,000 against $101,059,000 a year ago. Operating loss was $99,000 against income of $6,500,000 a year ago. Income before income taxes was $1,119,000 against $7,390,000 a year ago. Net income was $5,025,000 against $27,523,000 a year ago. Net income was $683,000 against $5,024,000 a year ago. Basic and diluted income per share was $0.02 against $0.13 a year ago. EBITDA was $5,747,000 against $12,389,000 a year ago. Adjusted net income was $5,748,000 or $0.15 per diluted share against or $11,668,000 or $0.30 per Diluted share a year ago.

The company is maintaining guidance for the full-year 2017 as follows: Revenue is expected to be in the range of $180 million to $190 million, and operating income as a percentage of revenue, excluding amortization of purchased intangible assets, is projected to be in the range of 1% to 5%.


VASCO Presents at In|Vest 2017, Jul-11-2017 12:00 PM
Jul 8 17
VASCO Presents at In|Vest 2017, Jul-11-2017 12:00 PM. Venue: New York Marriott Marquis, 1535 Broadway, New York 10036, New York, United States. Speakers: Michael Pupil, Sales Manager, eSignLive.


